Data Safety Declaration
1. Does the app collect or share user data?

Yes. The app collects limited technical and usage data for analytics and performance monitoring purposes.
The app does not sell user data and does not share data with third parties for advertising or marketing purposes.

2. Types of Data Collected
App Activity

Data Collected:

App interactions (such as screens viewed and feature usage)

Purpose:

Analytics

App functionality improvement

Shared:

No

Device or Other Identifiers

Data Collected:

Device model

Operating system version

Anonymous device identifiers

Purpose:

App functionality

Performance monitoring

Analytics

Shared:

No

Crash Logs

Data Collected:

Crash reports

Diagnostic information

Performance data

Purpose:

App stability improvements

Bug fixes

Performance monitoring

Shared:

No

3. Data Not Collected

The app does not collect:

Names

Email addresses

Phone numbers

Precise location

Approximate location

Advertising identifiers

Payment information

User account data

The app does not display advertisements and does not use advertising identifiers.

4. Data Usage Purposes

Collected data is used strictly for:

Maintaining and improving app functionality

Monitoring app stability and performance

Understanding general feature usage trends

Data is not used for advertising or marketing.

5. Data Encryption

All data transmitted through Google Play Services and Firebase services is encrypted in transit using industry-standard security protocols.

6. Data Deletion

Phasmophobia Companion does not require user accounts and does not store personal user data.

Users may uninstall the app at any time to stop further data collection.

